title: Wednesday Track Clinics
description: Every Wednesday, from April 30 through September 3, Chicago Velo Campus will host track clinics designed to introduce new riders to track racing, and to provide effective and focused training sessions for experienced track racers.
course: Clinics will consist of four, four-week focused sessions, including juniors, beginning riders, experienced racers, and event specific training.  Also within the season will be three, one-day clinics with topics to be announced.
registration: Please register on our website:  www.chicagovelocampus.com or like us on Facebook to register through our Facebook events.

title: Afterglow - A Cyclocross Race
description: Bringin' it back for the fifth year, Afterglow - A Cyclocross Race promises to be you favorite final race of the Chicago season. Do it for the kids!
course:
COURSE INFORMATION
1.5-mile spectator-friendly course through a park in the city. Typical cyclocross course shenanigans.
registration:
REGISTRATION
• Race day registration opens at 9:00AM and closes 30 minutes before each race. Online registration closes the Thursday 
evening prior to the race.
• Register online at http://www.BikeReg.com. Day-Of Entry fees are cash (preferred) or check (bring cash). Preregistration 
will close when the combined registration reaches the 100-rider field limit.
• Day of registration incurs a $5 late fee. All riders must sign a USAC rider release form and City of Chicago waiver.
• 2nd or 3rd race of the day is $10, Pre-reg or day-of
• Cat 1/2/3 and Cat 3 choice should be however you want to match up for USAC rankings or CrossResults points. Events 
will be scored separately.
• * Single Speed Open Requirements: One usable gear and two working breaks
• ** Fatbike Open Requirements: 3.5” minimum tire size (as printed on tire)
• Etc category: must have wheels and a front brake. Tandems scored separately from whatever else was brought. No 
cyclocross bikes.
notes:
LICENSES 
All races will be held under USAC permit. Riders without an annual USAC license will be required to purchase a 1-day license for $15. Renew your annual license online at USACycling.org. Annual renewals will also be available at registration for $70, Juniors $35. Annual licenses purchased after Dec 1, 2014 are valid through Dec 31, 2015.

RULES
All USAC rules apply. Helmets must be worn at all times while riding a bicycle at the race venue. High-Fives for wearing 
an aero helmet.

CATEGORY DESCRIPTION
Beginners: One-Day licenses holders must race Category 5, Women Cat 4, Masters, Juniors, or Single Speed, even Fatbike/etc category. Please check your 2014 USAC license. If you disagree with your CX category apply for an upgrade at USACycling.org.
